lets talk about why we want to make changea in your lives tough subject it can be ill go first in this picture is one of my whys for striving for a healthier life my kids are my world this guy here has a rare genetic syndrome autism and he doesnt talk his future is always my worry i wonder who will take care of him when i am old and cant physically do it scares me immensely in my marathon toward my finish line i will live the fittest and best life i can will i hit a wall and slide smashed to the ground sure with i have times where i am a super sprinter absolutely will i hit the finish line perfectly no way will i fight the entire race with consistency and intention you betcha whats your why think about it then get out there and put in the effort for your why

lets talk about migraine headaches for a minute do you get them i do they suck sometimes they really cramp my style keep me down when i want to be out running around delay my days many times i have had to power through them and get my kids to the doctor or to an important school meeting i cant skip these things planned months ahead groups gathered to love and assist my children in their learning and behavior many times headaches have gotten in the way of my ability to exercise doing cardio or lifting light weights with a migraine is puke worthy for me what i have found is that i can still manage to eat within my plan and still make good choices my gift to myself even when i feel crummy nobody is perfect most certainly not me and that is ok every day i give myself the best care i can the most important is that i take the opportunity to try how are you going to slide around your obstacles and care for yourself this weekend think about it take the chance you are worth it
take care of yourself

five months into the quarantine i turned 46 for sure one of the weirder years of my life my baby turned 13 my oldest will be able to buy alcohol and my middle guy if he wasnt handicapped would be getting his drivers license and like everyone with kids we started our home bound school adventure midmarch its been a strange one ive lost myself this year in many ways but also had a chance to slow down and find the real me ive found out what and who is really important to who i am and really thought about what i want and who i want to be when the bottom drops out and normal goes out the window its a really good time to take a good look in the mirror im working on that girl in the mirror working on making changes also working on loving myself right where i am im certain that i am where i am supposed to be right now and i know that i have the courage and power to change what needs to be shifted to be where i should be in the future

the last 5 months have been a nightmare and a gift in one way i am absolutely isolated in my home or car from doing anything having a daughter with an immunodeficiency cvid has kept me running scared a regular germ can send her spiraling down hill fast and to the hospital a covid infection would be devastating my boy ryan and his ultra rare genetic syndrome autism just cant handle an illness the powers of the coronavirus and both boys have celiac disease an autoimmune disease and many other food and environmental allergies to top it off ryan simply cantwont wear a mask pretty much leaves us to drives in the country and lots of home time the blessings come in the time gifted to us with no appointments and no buildings we can enter we have spent so many hours out exploring our area state parks new lakes farm areas amish country sonic happy hours chipotl to go and so much more the hours we have spent out in nature this summer are priceless this social isolation from others has truly been a gift we have laughed more and gotten dirtier than ever before and we rescued sister cats as school looms close i am trying to make sure we dont loose this free spirited time we have found to just be us have you been blessed by the slower pace of isolation

banksy basquiat keith haring this piece and another just across the street is up between the underground station and the venue for the design leadership conference ive been attending this week more on that later pretty damn cool to see this kind of thing in person

become a better design leader thats the reason i came to london to attend a design conference unlike any ive been to before it was to put it lightly incredible attendees and speakers came from around the world and from organizations huge ge ibm spotify etc and small agencies 5 person startups etc no matter the size of their organization or team most were struggling with similar things albeit at different scales things like team structure stakeholder management do i even know what im doing taking advantage of designs relatively new seat at the table etc it was a bit of a kumbaya were all figuring out the same shit as we go time which is insanely reassuring but also a lot of mba for design type sessions that i know will help me and my team do more meaningful work that stuff will take me quite a while to process photo baker street tube station my departure point each morning to get to the conference journal design

when i lived in dc every year there was a day i referred to as tom petty day it was a different day every year and you never knew when it would be but you know when it arrived a warm sunny spring day when you first felt that the weather had turned a corner from sometimes warmsometimes cold to consistently warm in the sun and the warmth id realize tom petty day was upon us open the windows hit play on pettys greatest hits cd and make things official with the first few notes of american girl i loved tom petty day i was sad when i realized there is no tom petty day in san francisco the weather just isnt consistent or predictable enough you never feel like the sun and warmth will stay for a more than a few days certainly not for months and so now i celebrate the occasional tom petty one desperate moment when the weather is spectacular and the fog lifts outside and in well she was an american girl raised on promises why tom petty cause i nearly wore that cd out spring semester freshman year of college and as a result associate it strongly with a bright warm dc spring day nothing more to it than that well that and the fact that tom petty was awesome

aps is arizonas largest utility it has a monopoly over the electricity business in much of the state a monopoly over something everyone has to buy is a pretty good thing to have if youre into making money and aps is very into making money half a billion dollars in profit last year alone but aps is never satisfied not with hundreds of millions in profits ceo don brandt personally took home millions all for selling something people could only buy from them and that they had to buy it gets hot in the summer in arizona like 115 degrees hot daily for long stretches in weather like that you need air conditioning you need fans you need electricity or you die aps didnt need the fifty bucks or so that 72yearold stephanie pullman was a few days late in paying when aps decided to cut off her electricity on a 107 degree day but aps sure wanted it a week later the county sheriffs office found stephanie in her home dead of environmental heat exposure her body already decomposing this will become more common if we let it climate change will make hot days like that more common an economy rigged to allow wealthy corporations to do whatever they want in the name of making a buck will lead to more millionaires like don brandt too busy counting their cash to give a damn who dies when their electricity gets shut off if we let it
